  "description": "Factory maintenance schedule for the Leapmotor C10 (BEV / non-REEV), extracted from its official owner's manual. Base interval 20000 km / 12 months, whichever comes first. The C10 is essentially identical to the B10 EXCEPT tires: replace every 3 years / 50000 km, tread limit 3 mm (B10 is 40000 km / 1.6 mm; T03 is 60000 km / 3 mm). Confirmed identical to B10: brake fluid 2y/40000 km, coolant replacement 4y/40000 km, reducer oil 60000 km, reducer/drivetrain filter 60000 km, A/C cabin filter 1y/20000 km, tire rotation 10000 km (wheel-nut torque 170 +/- 10 N.m), wiper blades yearly, brake pad limit 2 mm friction, brake disc limit 26 mm front / 16 mm rear. This pack matches the C10 intervals previously extracted from the 194-page C10 manual and is now validated against Silvio's own C10 (BEV) manual. NOTE: this is the BEV C10 — the C10 REEV (range-extender) is out of scope (Mate is BEV-only) and would add engine oil/air filter/spark plugs/fuel filter not present here.",
